│ stop({"edit_points": [[504, 505, "llvm/lib/Analysis/MemorySSAUpdater.cpp"]], "thoughts":   │
│ "### 1. Understanding the Issue ###\nThe assertion failure occurs in                       │
│ `MemorySSAUpdater::fixupDefs` at line 504, where it checks if `MSSA->dominates(NewDef,     │
│ FirstDef)` is true. This indicates that the MemorySSA dominance relationship is violated,  │
│ which is a critical invariant for MemorySSA correctness.\n\n### 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log   │
│ ###\nThe `opt` log shows that the LICM pass is attempting to promote loop-invariant memory │
│ accesses. The failure occurs during the insertion of memory definitions (`insertDef`) in   │
│ the MemorySSA structure. The log also indicates unpredictable loop execution counts, which │
│ suggests complex control flow that may contribute to the dominance issue.\n\n### 3. Root   │
│ Cause Analysis ###\nThe debugger reveals that `NewDef` is a `MemoryPhi` in the block       │
